// full_demo.nc — NATCOM Full Feature Demonstration
// Shows: input, strings, boolean, math funcs, random, modulo,
//        repeat loops, while loops, swap, display, increment/decrement

// ── USER INPUT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
Create a floating point variable named A and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named B and set it to 0.
Create a string named Username and set it to "Guest".

Ask the user for text named Username.
Ask the user to enter a value for A.
Ask the user to enter a value for B.

// ── CALCULATOR ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
Create a floating point variable named Sum and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named Diff and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named Product and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named Quotient and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named Remainder and set it to 0.

Add A to Sum.
Add B to Sum.
Display the values of Sum.

Add A to Diff.
Subtract B from Diff.
Display the values of Diff.

Add A to Product.
Multiply Product by B.
Display the values of Product.

Add A to Quotient.
Divide Quotient by B.
Display the values of Quotient.

Find the remainder of A divided by B and store in Remainder.
Display the values of Remainder.

// ── MATH FUNCTIONS ──────────────────────────────────────────────
Create a floating point variable named SqrtA and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named PowerAB and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named AbsVal and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named MaxVal and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named MinVal and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named FloorVal and set it to 0.
Create a floating point variable named CeilVal and set it to 0.

Set SqrtA to the square root of A.
Set PowerAB to A to the power of B.
Set AbsVal to the absolute value of Diff.
Set MaxVal to the maximum of A and B.
Set MinVal to the minimum of A and B.
Set FloorVal to the floor of A.
Set CeilVal to the ceiling of A.

Display the values of SqrtA.
Display the values of PowerAB.
Display the values of AbsVal.
Display the values of MaxVal.
Display the values of MinVal.
Display the values of FloorVal.
Display the values of CeilVal.

// ── RANDOM NUMBERS ───────────────────────────────────────────────
Create a high speed integer named RandomRoll and set it to 0.
Generate a random number between 1 and 100 and store in RandomRoll.
Display the values of RandomRoll.

// ── BOOLEAN ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Create a boolean named IsActive and set it to true.
Create a boolean named IsExpired and set it to false.
Display the values of IsActive.

// ── INCREMENT / DECREMENT ────────────────────────────────────────
Create a high speed integer named Counter and set it to 0.
Increment Counter.
Increment Counter.
Increment Counter.
Decrement Counter.
Display the values of Counter.

// ── REPEAT LOOP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
Create a high speed integer named LoopSum and set it to 0.
Repeat 5 times:
  Increment LoopSum.
Done.
Display the values of LoopSum.

// ── SWAP ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Create a floating point variable named X and set it to 10.0.
Create a floating point variable named Y and set it to 20.0.
Swap the values of X and Y.
Display the values of X.
Display the values of Y.

// ── CONDITIONAL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
If the A is greater than B, then:
  Display "A is the larger number."
Otherwise:
  Display "B is the larger number."
